getExponent</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the target exponent is smaller than the given exponent, decreases the exponent of the mantissa to\nthe target exponent; otherwise does nothing.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.decreaseExponent","kind":"def","line":164,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.decreaseExponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L164-L170"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.roundWithAccuracy\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">roundWithAccuracy</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">sign</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Sign.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Sign\">Sign</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mantissa</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">exponent</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">accuracy</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\">Accuracy</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a finite float represented by a sign, mantissa and exponent, together with an\n`Accuracy` datum, round it to conform to the given `Format`.\n\nImportant: this function will only drop bits from the mantissa and increase the exponent,\nnot the other way around. The result will only conform to the given specification if\nthe exponent was not too large to begin with. If this may be the case, you should call\n`round` instead.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.roundWithAccuracy","kind":"def","line":140,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.roundWithAccuracy","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L140-L162"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.shiftToTargetExponent\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">shiftToTargetExponent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">spec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Format/Basic.html#Float.Model.Format\">Format</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mantissa</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">exponent</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">accuracy</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\">Accuracy</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa\">ExtendedMantissa</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the target exponent for the given mantissa and exponent and shifts the\nmantissa and exponent and initial accuracy to the target exponent, returning\nthe new extended mantissa and exponent.\n\nImportant: this function will only drop bits from the mantissa and increase the exponent,\nnot the other way around. The result will only conform to the given specification if\nthe exponent was not too large to begin with. If this may be the case, you should call\n`round` instead.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.shiftToTargetExponent","kind":"def","line":125,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.shiftToTargetExponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L125-L138"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.shiftToExponent\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">shiftToExponent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mantissa</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">exponent</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">accuracy</span> : <a hre