f=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa\">Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa.mk","kind":"ctor","line":57,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L57-L68"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">ExtendedMantissa</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Pairs a mantissa with two residual bits, the 'round bit' and the 'sticky bit',\nwhich carry precisely the required information to compute the `Accuracy` of the\nmantissa.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa","kind":"structure","line":57,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L57-L68"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.roundToNearestEven\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">Accuracy</span>.<span class=\"name\">roundToNearestEven</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mantissa</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\">Accuracy</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Rounds the given mantissa with the given accuracy according to the\nround-to-nearest strategy, with ties breaking in favor of even\nmantissas.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.roundToNearestEven","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.roundToNearestEven","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L44-L53"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.inexact\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">Accuracy</span>.<span class=\"name\">inexact</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">relativeToPlusOneHalfUlp</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord/Basic.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\">Accuracy</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The approximation is strictly smaller than the infinitely precise value,\nand the given `Ordering` describes the result of comparing the\ninfinitely precise value and the approximation plus half a ulp.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.inexact","kind":"ctor","line":35,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.inexact","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L35-L40"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.exact\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">Accuracy</span>.<span class=\"name\">exact</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\">Accuracy</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The approximation is exactly equal to the infinitely precise value.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.exact","kind":"ctor","line":31,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy.exact","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L31-L34"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">Accuracy</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Suppose given a real number `x : ℝ` with binary expansion\n`x = ± x₀.x₁x₂x₃…`. Truncating the expansion at some point gives an\napproximation of `x` as a floating-point number `y`. We can then ask how `y`\nis related to `x`. If `y` is exactly `x`, then we say that we are exact.\nOtherwise we are inexact, and `y` is slightly smaller than `x`, but `x` is also\nsmaller than `y + 1ulp`. Together with the information that we are inexact,\nwe store the information of where `x` is located relative to `y + ½ulp`. This\nis sufficient information for rounding `y` according to the various IEEE rounding\nrules.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy","kind":"inductive","line":19,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.Accuracy","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Round.lean#L19-L40"}}],"imports":["Init.Data.Float.Model.Format.Basic","Init.Data.Float.Model.Unpacked.Basic","Init.Data.Float.Model.Unpacked.Sign"],"instances":[{"className":"HShiftRight","name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa.instHShiftRightNat","typeNames":["Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa","Nat","Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.ExtendedMantissa"]}],"name":"Init.Data.Float.Model.Unpacked.Round"}